programme.title: The Open Live
programme.desc: Coverage of the first day of the prestigious event, which takes place at Carnoustie Golf Links in Angus, with Jordan Spieth taking to the tee as the reigning champion. The American shot a five-under 65 on the opening day of last year's tournament at Royal Birkdale, which saw him take a share of the lead with compatriots Brooks Koepka and Matt Kuchar. He would finish each of the next three days at the top of the leaderboard, and in lifting the Claret Jug became only the second player in history to win three of the four majors before turning 24, following in the illustrious footsteps of Jack Nicklaus.(n)

programme.title: The Open Live
programme.desc: Coverage of the second day of the prestigious event, which takes place at Carnoustie Golf Links in Angus, as the players aim to make the cut ahead of the weekend's play. Day two of last year's tournament at Royal Birkdale was blighted by testing weather conditions, which led to just eight players carding an under-par round. While eventual champion Jordan Spieth managed to take sole position at the top of the leaderboard following a one-under 69 to claim an overall score of six under par, a host of former champions would fare less well, as the likes of Phil Mickelson, Louis Oosthuizen and Darren Clarke missed the cut.(n)

programme.title: College Football Playoff Semifinal: Rose Bowl: Georgia vs. Oklahoma
programme.desc: Georgia (12-1) vs. Oklahoma (12-1). From the Rose Bowl in Pasadena, Cal. Heisman Trophy winner Baker Mayfield (41 TDs, 5 INTs) QBs the Sooners under 34-year-old head coach Lincoln Riley, while Georgia leans on senior RBs Nick Chubb and Sony Michel. This is the teams' first meeting and second Rose Bowl appearance for each, with the Bulldogs winning after the 1942 season and OU romping on New Year's Day 2003. (cc).(n)

programme.title: College Football Playoff Semifinal: Sugar Bowl: Alabama vs. Clemson
programme.desc: Alabama (11-1) vs. Clemson (12-1). From Mercedes-Benz Superdome in New Orleans. Coaches Nick Saban and Dabo Swinney meet again after splitting the last two CFP title games. Tackles Raekwon Davis and Christian Wilkins anchor defenses that rank 1-2 in ppg. At QB, Tide sophomore Jalen Hurts has thrown one INT all season and looks to improve on his 13-for-31 night vs. Clemson last year. Tigers junior Kelly Bryant (24 total TDs) operates behind three first-team All-ACC linemen. (cc).(n)

programme.desc: Part 2. A true story of conservation success, Trevon heads back to Kentucky with the Tackett family to help 11-year-old Ashton Tackett on his first bull elk hunt.(n)

programme.title: Old School Outdoors
programme.desc: Part 1. Greg Hal and Dennis Branton head to South Dakota for a trip they have had on their bucket list for many years. They head to Cheyenne Ridge to chase pheasants across the prairies.(n)

programme.title: In-Fisherman
programme.desc: The focus is on hardcore presentation fundamentals that is the key to fishing success, as the staff spider rigs for super slab crappies, uses grub grinding tactics for mid-summery smallmouths and pitches softbaits for walleyes pushed shallow by wind.(n)

programme.title: Reel Time With Florida Sportsman
programme.desc: A tribute to the "Silver King," featuring everything you need to know about tarpon. Learn why tarpon are one of Florida's most popular and important gamefish.(n)

programme.title: North American Whitetail Television
programme.desc: Gordon Whittington heads north to his personal Missouri farm for some crossbow action, Dr. Deer discusses balancing expectations on a small hunting property, and Pat Hogan explores the latest in crossbow technology from TenPoint.(n)

programme.title: Adrenaline
programme.desc: Preparation mixed planning is the recipe for success as the crew gear up for the Midwest whitetail bow season. Strategic food plot placement, treestands and mock scrapes will make or break the entire season.(n)

programme.title: Whitetail Explorer
programme.desc: The crew hunts early-season bucks in Kentucky.(n)

programme.title: Trained Assassins
programme.desc: Cragg Fitz heads to Wyoming to Seven J Outfitters to hunt with David Blanton and the guys from Realtree. This is a dream come true for Mr. Fitz.(n)

programme.title: Red Rising
programme.desc: Jason Bowers takes his friend Lindsey out hunting in Virginia. Jason has her on a buck in Virginia, however, the result ends differently than expected.(n)

programme.title: Dominant Bucks
programme.desc: Learn DIY bowhunting strategies from real hunters hunting wild dominant bucks. Join Illinois bowhunter Doug Fredericksen and Missouri bowhunter Fred Dunn as they find, set up and arrow mature dominant bucks.(n)

programme.title: Gun Stories
programme.desc: The Winchester Model 1873 is examined.(n)

programme.title: Guns & Gear
programme.desc: Crisp vision with ATN's X-Sight 4K Pro. Plus, Springfield Armory's 1911 Pro, Timney Triggers' SIG MPX trigger, Precision Match bullets from Barnes Bullets, Smith & Wesson's M&P Shield M2.0 family with Crimson Trace lasers and Legacy Sport's rifles.(n)

programme.title: Southern Addiction TV *
programme.desc: Pops has been having terrible luck hog hunting the last few weeks, but he is determined to have redemption on these south Georgia hogs.(n)

programme.title: Huntin' the Backwoods
programme.desc: Dan and Troy return to Newfoundland Adventures for another spring bear hunt with Todd and Laura Wiseman. Troy is shocked as he encounters not one, but two three-legged bears on the island, and Dan tags another Newfoundland bear.(n)

programme.title: The Lindsey Way
programme.desc: Still in Colorado, the crew lays down some of the most memorable elk hunting they've ever encountered. David takes it to the bottom of the ninth for a hunt of a lifetime.(n)

programme.title: BuckVentures Outdoors
programme.desc: Jeff Danker heads to Montana to hunt Jackie Bushman's ranch in a shot at redemption for last year's trip.(n)

programme.title: Savage Outdoors
programme.desc: Mike and the crew are in Illinois hunting the Grigsby Farm with their bows. The rut is heating up and the big bucks are on the move.(n)

programme.title: Petersen's Hunting Adventures
programme.desc: With his Mozambique forest bull in the salt, Craig sets his sights on the Marromeu Grasslands in pursuit of a swamp buffalo.(n)

programme.title: Jim Shockey's Hunting Adventures
programme.desc: Jim travels to Mozambique to go after man-eating crocodiles that have been terrorizing local villagers.(n)

programme.title: Jim Shockey's Hunting Adventures
programme.desc: Jim heads to Argentina to hunt black buck and fallow deer but decides to change plans after he spots a rare free range red stag. Also: a problem buffalo has been harassing the local farmers.(n)

programme.title: Whitetail Frenzy
programme.desc: After missing a birthday opportunity on his target buck in Ohio, pro-staffer Elijah Bennett is back at it one year later hoping for birthday redemption.(n)

programme.title: Out-There TV
programme.desc: Corey Brossman has been watching his deer grow in Delaware during the summer months in hopes of his kids have an early-season opportunity with the Excalibur crossbow. Brody Brossman is only four-years-old, but hunts like a pro.(n)
